      <title>Como criar um site acadêmico no R</title>
      <link>https://mauriciovancine.github.io/pt/post/2020-12-30-como-criar-um-site-academico-no-r/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 30 Dec 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://mauriciovancine.github.io/pt/post/2020-12-30-como-criar-um-site-academico-no-r/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Que o &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.r-project.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt; possui múltiplas utilidades para análise e visualização de dados de &lt;a href=&#34;https://cran.r-project.org/web/views/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;diversos formatos&lt;/a&gt; e em &lt;a href=&#34;https://data-flair.training/blogs/r-applications/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;diversas áreas&lt;/a&gt; é indiscutível. Entretanto, a união dessa linguagem com o &lt;a href=&#34;https://pt.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Markdown&lt;/a&gt;, dando origem ao &lt;a href=&#34;https://rmarkdown.rstudio.com/index.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;RMarkdown&lt;/a&gt;, aliada ao IDE &lt;a href=&#34;https://rstudio.com/products/rstudio/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;RStudio&lt;/a&gt; ainda pode ser novidade para muitas pessoas. Essa junção permite diversas possibilidades de criação de &lt;a href=&#34;https://bookdown.org/yihui/rmarkdown/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;aplicações complementares ao R&lt;/a&gt;. Pretendo escrever mais sobre essa união e utilidades num post futuro.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neste post, vou focar nos passos para a criação de um site acadêmico no R, uma forma bem interessante que achei de desafiar meu conhecimento até então, e principalmente minha paciência&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Existem várias formas de criar um &lt;a href=&#34;https://wowchemy.com/templates/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;site acadêmico&lt;/a&gt;, mas focarei aqui no formato que consegui fazer de forma mais rápida e tranquila, usando o pacote &lt;a href=&#34;https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/blogdown/index.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;blogdown&lt;/a&gt;, hospedando no &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;github&lt;/a&gt;, com esse formato: &amp;lt;username.github.io&amp;gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://git-scm.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;git&lt;/a&gt;, e o &lt;a href=&#34;https://rstudio.com/products/rstudio/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;RStudio&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Todas as informações referentes à criação e onfiguração do site podem ser consultadas no livro do pacote &lt;a href=&#34;https://bookdown.org/yihui/blogdown/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;blogdown: Creating Websites with R Markdown&lt;/a&gt;, do &lt;a href=&#34;https://yihui.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Yihui Xie&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Outra fonte de informação são os geniais posts da &lt;a href=&#34;https://alison.rbind.io/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Profa. Alison Hill&lt;/a&gt;. Deixo eles listados em destaque aqui:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://alison.rbind.io/post/2017-06-12-up-and-running-with-blogdown/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Up &amp;amp; Running with blogdown&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://alison.rbind.io/post/2019-02-19-hugo-archetypes/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;A Spoonful of Hugo: Archetypes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://alison.rbind.io/post/2019-02-19-hugo-netlify-toml/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;A Spoonful of Hugo: The netlify.toml File&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://alison.rbind.io/post/2019-02-21-hugo-page-bundles/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;A Spoonful of Hugo: Page Bundles&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://alison.rbind.io/post/2019-03-04-hugo-troubleshooting/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;A Spoonful of Hugo: Troubleshooting Your Build&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://alison.rbind.io/post/2020-12-12-how-much-hugo/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;A Spoonful of Hugo: How much Hugo do I need to know?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://alison.rbind.io/post/2020-12-27-blogdown-checks/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Unbreak your blogdown site&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fundamental destacar que só encontrei um &lt;a href=&#34;https://diegopftrindade.netlify.app/post/blogdown-tutorial-in-portuguese/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;post&lt;/a&gt; em português do &lt;a href=&#34;https://diegopftrindade.netlify.app/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Diego Trindade&lt;/a&gt;. Nele é possível ler mais informações e também uma discussão muito legal sobro o porquê criar e manter um site acadêmico.&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;h2 id=&#34;passos-para-criação-do-site&#34;&gt;Passos para criação do site&lt;a href=&#34;#passos-para-cria%c3%a7%c3%a3o-do-site&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;anchor-symbol&#34; height=&#34;26&#34; width=&#34;26&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 22 22&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;
&lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;
&lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76.0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71.0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71.0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76.0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Os passos à seguir seguem essa listagem:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GitHub&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RStudio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Git&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;blogdown&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Edição do site&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;



&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-github&#34;&gt;1. GitHub&lt;a href=&#34;#1-github&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;anchor-symbol&#34; height=&#34;26&#34; width=&#34;26&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 22 22&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;
&lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;
&lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76.0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71.0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71.0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76.0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Primeiramente é necessário criar duas contas on-line:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GitHub: &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/&#34;&gt;https://github.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Criar um repositório no GitHub&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Com a conta do GitHub feita, será necessário &lt;a href=&#34;https://help.github.com/pt/github/getting-started-with-github/create-a-repo&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;criar um
repositório&lt;/a&gt;.
Eu criei com o nome de &amp;ldquo;mauriciovancine2&amp;rdquo;, só de exemplo, mas pode ser
qualquer outro.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;criar_repositorio.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Criar um repositório no GitHub NO README + NO .gitignore (ainda!)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;clonar o repositório - git clone File &amp;gt; New Project &amp;gt; Version
Control &amp;gt; Git&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RStudio: install.packages(&amp;ldquo;blogdown&amp;rdquo;) library(blogdown)
new_site(theme = &amp;ldquo;gcushen/hugo-academic&amp;rdquo;, sample = TRUE,
theme_example = TRUE, empty_dirs = TRUE, to_yaml = TRUE)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Conferir a versão do Hugo &lt;a href=&#34;https://themes.gohugo.io/academic/&#34;&gt;https://themes.gohugo.io/academic/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;is your version less than the minimum version? hugo_version()&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;if yes, then do this update_hugo(force = TRUE)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;4&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Netlify segure e arraste a pasta public/ para
&lt;a href=&#34;https://app.netlify.com/drop&#34;&gt;https://app.netlify.com/drop&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;criar um arquivo &amp;ldquo;netlify.toml&amp;rdquo; file.create(&amp;ldquo;netlify.toml&amp;rdquo;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open, then copy &amp;amp; paste:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[build] publish = &amp;ldquo;public&amp;rdquo; command = &amp;ldquo;hugo&amp;rdquo;
[context.production.environment] HUGO_VERSION = &amp;ldquo;0.58.2&amp;rdquo; HUGO_ENV =
&amp;ldquo;production&amp;rdquo; HUGO_ENABLEGITINFO = &amp;ldquo;true&amp;rdquo;
[context.branch-deploy.environment] HUGO_VERSION = &amp;ldquo;0.58.2&amp;rdquo;
[context.deploy-preview.environment] HUGO_VERSION = &amp;ldquo;0.58.2&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;6&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;linkar o site com o GitHub no Netlify&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;



&lt;h2 id=&#34;2-rstudio&#34;&gt;2. RStudio&lt;a href=&#34;#2-rstudio&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;anchor-symbol&#34; height=&#34;26&#34; width=&#34;26&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 22 22&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;
